What you need to know:

This weekend’s tournament has received an overwhelming entry of 160 players with Machakos Golf Club, the virtual home of the ICEA Lion King of the course, leading with the largest entry of 34 playersDuring last year’s tournament which was the last in the 2020 series following the cancellation of the others because of Covid-19 pandemic, Kim Nderitu, a member of both Nanyuki and Thika Sports Club, beat a field of 102 golfers to emerge the overall winnerElsewhere, the hunt for points towards the Kenya Amateur Golf Championship (KAGC) series and World Amateur Ranking gets underway with 62nd edition of the annual Sigona Bowl at Sigona Golf Club where a field of 96 players was drawn